title: mysql async breaks compiler by during compiling connection string

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
<!--
Thank you for finding an Internal Compiler Error! 🧊  If possible, try to provide
a minimal verifiable example. You can read "Rust Bug Minimization Patterns" for
how to create smaller examples.

http://blog.pnkfx.org/blog/2019/11/18/rust-bug-minimization-patterns/

-->

### Code

```Rust
use mysql_async::Row;
use mysql_async::prelude::*;
use mysql_async::prelude::WithParams;
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
use serde_sheets::{get_sheets, service_account_from_env};
use rust_decimal_macros::dec;
use rust_decimal::Decimal;
const DOCUMENT_ID: &str = "1yHZvGrNPx_mGImYCZaB4KHBgoSxfflQzGk7XCCgRTKg";
const TAB_NAME: &str = "Hoja 1";

#[derive(Debug, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
struct ExampleObject {
    name: String,
    number_of_foos: u64,
}

#[derive(Debug, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
struct InfoCubeRow{
    cost_data_id: String,
    work_order : String,
    activity_code : String,
    activity : String,
    terrain_code : String,
    terrain : String,
    status : String,
    cost_element : String,
    cost_object_code : String,
    cost_object : String,
    qty : Decimal,
    unit : String,
    unit_cost : Decimal,
    cost : Decimal,
}

async fn read_from_mysql(dbname: &str) -> Result<Vec<InfoCubeRow>, Box<dyn std::error::Error>>{
    let database_url = format!("mysql://root:1234qwerasdF@localhost:3307/{dbname}");

    let pool = mysql_async::Pool::new(&database_url);
    let mut conn = pool.get_conn().await?;

    let loaded_payments = "SELECT * from infocube_costs,"
	.with(())
	.map::<_,InfoCubeRow,_,_>(&mut conn, |row: Row|{

	    InfoCubeRow{
		cost_data_id: row.take::<String,_>("cost_data_id").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		work_order : row.take::<String,_> ("work order").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		activity_code : row.take::<String,_> ("activity_code").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		activity : row.take::<String,_> ("activity").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		terrain_code : row.take::<String,_> ("terrain code").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		terrain : row.take::<String,_> ("terrain").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		status : row.take::<String,_> ("status").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		cost_element : row.take::<String,_> ("Cost Element").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		cost_object_code : row.take::<String,_> ("Cost Object Code").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		cost_object : row.take::<String,_> ("Cost Object").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		qty : row.take::<Decimal,_> ("Qty").unwrap_or(dec!(0.0)),
		unit : row.take::<String,_> ("Unit").unwrap_or("(empty)".to_string()),
		unit_cost : row.take::<Decimal,_> ("Unit Cost").unwrap_or(dec!(0.0)),
		cost : row.take::<Decimal,_> ("Cost").unwrap_or(dec!(0.0)),
	    }

	})
	.await?;

    Ok(loaded_payments)

}

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {

    let args = std::env::args();
    if let (_,Some(dbname)) = (args.next(), args.next()) {

	let service_account = service_account_from_env().unwrap();
	let mut sheets = get_sheets(service_account, Some("token_cache.json"))
	    .await
	    .unwrap();

	let objects = read_from_mysql(50);

	// write first 45 rows to sheet
	serde_sheets::write_page(&mut sheets, DOCUMENT_ID, TAB_NAME, objects)
	    .await
	    .unwrap();

	// append last 5 rows
	for obj in &objects[45..50] {
	    serde_sheets::append_row(&mut sheets, DOCUMENT_ID, TAB_NAME, obj)
		.await
		.unwrap();
	}

	// fetch all rows
	let returned: Vec<ExampleObject> = serde_sheets::read_all(&mut sheets, DOCUMENT_ID, TAB_NAME)
	    .await
	    .unwrap();

	// check data is same
	assert_eq!(objects, returned);
    }
}

```
